JOHANNESBURG - Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba is expected to outline government s inclusive economic plan of action on Thursday morning.READ: Gigaba and co look for economic directionLast month, Gigaba said it seemed highly unlikely South Africa would meet Treasury s own growth forecast of 1.3% for 2017.The country is dealing with credit rating downgrades and high unemployment.Gigaba said he would look at prioritising funds and cutting spending where possible. The briefing is scheduled for 11:30 on Thursday morning. It will be streamed live on eNCA.com.eNCA